<p>I have this code:</p>  <pre><code>class Super{     public static List&lt;Super&gt; methodA() { . . . } } class Sub:Super{     public static List&lt;Sub&gt; methodA() { . . . } } </code></pre>  <p>Then I call :</p>  <pre><code> Sub.methodA(); </code></pre>  <p>But the executed is from super class. Anyway I can exec the subclass's static method? They has <strong>same static method name</strong>.</p>  <p>Update: <a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/vSPi4.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/vSPi4.png" alt="enter image description here"></a> You can see that Product is my superclass and purchase is subclass. Both has same static getAll() but returned different type. In this case it returns the List</p>